<p>This project is a cloud implementation of fast-neural-style in PyTorch. A React app was deployed in Heroku that can funcitons image style transformation via designed AWS cloud architecture and several Rest APIs. The application can be found at <a href="https://fast-transfer-style-ap.herokuapp.com/">here</a>.</p>

<h1 style="text-align: center;">EECS545-Implementation of XGBoost</h1>

<p>This project is focused on the implementation of the ensemble learning algorithm
XGBoost and the interpretability of its prediction. We implement XGBoost as well
as its built-in methods for calculating the feature importance from the scratch. We
apply XGboost on Higgs and Adult census income dataset and conduct feature
selection methods to better understand the model decision and thus improve the
efficiency by reducing the model size and training time. We confirmed our im-
plementation of XGBoost by achieving similar performance to the official library
on the Higgs dataset. We also leverage a game theoretical approach Tree SHAP
(SHapley Additive exPlanation) and compare its results with the built-in methods
both in performance and interpretability. By designed experiments, we explore
the improvement and interpretability between different feature selection methods
of XGBoost. Using the best feature selection method on the adult census income
dataset we were able to reduce the training dimensions by 1/3 while reducing the
test accuracy by only 0.007%</p>
